cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper proposes a new network architecture for semantic segmentation, which is a popular computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a novel attention mechanism, which involves learning long-range dependencies, and this could fall under the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of GPU memory and computational efficiency, which could be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
